# Android Tutorium

## I. Definitions

### a) Android Manifest (AndroidManifest.xml)
Manifest glues everythings concerning the application. 
It is the file that explaining what the app consist of. specfy the main 
building block, what permission are requires and so on. 

### b) Ressources Files

### b.1) Layout XML 
Locating in path `res/layout` , his purpose is to specify the layout 
of the screen. 

### b.2) String 
Location in paht `res/values/strings`, he contains all the text used in 
the application. </br>
Example of String resources 

```
<!--store in res/values/strings.xml-->
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<resources>
   <string name="hello">Hello World, HelloWorld!</string>
   <string name="app_name">Hello, World!!!</string>
</resources>
```

### b.3) The R.java file 
The R file is the glue between the world of Java and the world of resources .
It is an automatically generated file, and as such, you never modify it. It is
recreated every time you change anything in the res directory, for example, 
when you add an image or XML file.

### c) Android application 
An android Application is a loose collection of Services, Activities,
ContentProvider and BroadcastReceiver.  
